0003151c    uint32_t periodic_comm_update_task()

0003151c  // Periodic communication task called from main loop.
0003151c  // Increments counter data_20005771 every cycle.
0003151c  // Every 4th cycle: checks STM ready (data_20005c73), sets
0003151c  // comm_ready_flag.
0003151c  // Calls send_motor_status_msg() if data_2000519e==0.
0003151c  // Sends two NRF protocol messages with data from
0003151c  // 0x200031ec/0x20003200.
0003151c  // Updates setting 0xc if CAN filter (data_20005c68) changed.
0003151c  // Manages UARTSTM communication handshake and periodic data
0003151c  // exchange.
0003151c  00b5       push    {lr}
0003151e  83b0       sub     sp, #0xc
00031520  fef788fd   bl      #0x30034
00031524  90f82630   ldrb    r3, [r0, #0x26]
00031528  13b1       cbz     r3, #0x31530

0003152a  03b0       add     sp, #0xc
0003152c  5df804fb   pop     {pc}

00031534  1f4a       ldr     r2, [pc, #0x7c]
00031536  1378       ldrb    r3, [r2]
00031538  591c       adds    r1, r3, #1
0003153a  1170       strb    r1, [r2]
0003153c  13f0030f   tst     r3, #3
00031540  0bd1       bne     #0x3155a

00031548  dbb1       cbz     r3, #0x31582

0003154c  0122       movs    r2, #1
0003154e  83f86020   strb    r2, [r3, #0x60]

0003182c    int32_t stm_firmware_update_state_machine()

0003182c  // STM firmware update state machine. 6 states: 1=send_init,

00032294    int32_t load_system_state_from_fds()

00032294  // Load system state from FDS (Flash Data Storage).
00032294  // Reads 5-byte record via fds_close_record into var_10 buffer.
00032294  // If read fails, sets defaults:
00032294  // - data_20005d70=0 (orientation), data_20005d72/74=0x17/0x18
00032294  // - g_display_unit_system=2, data_20005d77=0x50 (brightness)
00032294  // - data_20005d78=0x4b (timeout), data_20005d79=1
00032294  // If read succeeds, loads values and mirrors to data_20005d8c-90.
00032294  // Adjusts data_20005d72/74 based on orientation (swaps 0x17/0x18).
00032294  // Copies settings to data_20005d7c backup, clears data_20005e90
00032294  // buffer.
00032294  // Initializes dispatch table from g_dispatch_table_entry_1 (176
00032294  // bytes, 0xb0).
00032294  // Searches for mode=2 entry to set data_20005d6d index.
00032294  // Restores saved configuration on boot.
00032294  10b5       push    {r4, lr}
00032296  82b0       sub     sp, #8
00032298  0522       movs    r2, #5
0003229a  0021       movs    r1, #0

0003237c    char const* const save_display_settings_to_fds()

0003237c  // Save display settings to FDS if changed.
0003237c  // Compares current settings with cached values (data_20005d8c-90):
0003237c  // - data_20005d77: brightness/contrast
0003237c  // - data_20005d78: screen timeout
0003237c  // - data_20005d70: orientation
0003237c  // - g_display_unit_system: units (metric/imperial)
0003237c  // - data_20005d79: other display option
0003237c  // If changed, packs to data_200034e8 and writes via
0003237c  // fds_write_file3_key71.
0003237c  // Returns status string: \"Settings save success\", \"No changes\",
0003237c  // \"Err 1\", \"Err 2\".
0003237c  // Prevents unnecessary flash writes by change detection.
0003237c  10b5       push    {r4, lr}
0003237e  fff729ff   bl      #0x321d4
00032382  0278       ldrb    r2, [r0]
00032384  1e4b       ldr     r3, [pc, #0x78]
00032386  db79       ldrb    r3, [r3, #7]
00032388  9a42       cmp     r2, r3
0003238a  04d1       bne     #0x32396

000324c4    int32_t lcd_power_off()

000324c4  // Power down LCD display. Sends sleep command to controller, disables
000324c4  // backlight PWM (P0.22), and asserts chip select to reduce power
000324c4  // consumption.

000324c8  f1f7c6f8   bl      #0x23658

000324da  f1f7e9f8   bl      #0x236b0

000324ee    uint32_t lcd_init()

000324ee  // Initialize LCD display hardware
000324ee  // Disables GPIOTE sense on channel 2
000324ee  // Uninitializes button system if initialized
000324ee  // Configures GPIO pins: P0.24, P0.23, P0.2 as disconnected (mode 4)
000324ee  // Returns result of gpiote_uninit_all()
000324ee  // Part of LCD initialization sequence

000324f2  f1f7b1f8   bl      #0x23658
000324f6  0220       movs    r0, #2

0003251c    void button_event_handler(uint8_t button_id, uint8_t press_type)

0003251c  // Main button event handler - processes button presses for 3 buttons
0003251c  // arg1(button_id): 0=left, 1=middle, 2=right button
0003251c  // arg2(press_type): 1=?, 2=short press, 3=medium press(1-2s), 4=?,
0003251c  // 5=long press(>2s), 6=?, 7=debounce
0003251c  // State machine (data_20005d6f) handling:
0003251c  // - State 2: Boot screen, button 0 short press -> State 1
0003251c  // - State 6/8 (Main): Button 0 short -> cycle drive mode (0-3),
0003251c  // Button 1/2 -> adjust assist (0-4)
0003251c  // - State 6/8: Button 2 long press + data_20005d79==1 +
0003251c  // data_2000519d==2 -> State 9, toggle dual output
0003251c  // - State 6/8: Button 1 long press -> State 10, toggle boolean flag,
0003251c  // Button 0 long press -> State 12 (trip reset confirm)
0003251c  // - State 7 (Settings): Button 0 short -> cycle menu item (6 items),
0003251c  // Button 1/2 -> adjust selected setting
0003251c  //   Menu items: 0=brightness(0-100), 1=unit system(0-2),
0003251c  // 2=orientation(0-1), 3=contrast(0-100), 4=?, 5=?
0003251c  // - State 7: Button 2 long press at menu item 4 -> Factory reset
0003251c  // sequence (deletes BLE peers, erases ext flash, resets all settings)
0003251c  // - State 11/12/13/14: Various confirmation screens
0003251c  // Special: Sends "$NRF,STM,EXT3V3,EN" UART command after factory
0003251c  // reset
0003251c  // CRITICAL state machine hub for all user interactions
0003251c  f0b5       push    {r4, r5, r6, r7, lr}
0003251e  93b0       sub     sp, #0x4c
00032520  0446       mov     r4, r0
00032522  0d46       mov     r5, r1

00032528  af49       ldr     r1, [pc, #0x2bc]

00032530  05a8       add     r0, sp, #0x14

0003253c  ab4b       ldr     r3, [pc, #0x2ac]
0003253e  93f800c0   ldrb    r12, [r3]

00032cc8    int32_t button_timer_processor()

00032cc8  // Process button timers for 3 buttons (data_200034d4 array).
00032cc8  // Calculates elapsed time since last event for each button.
00032cc8  // Button states in data_200034d4 (0/3=idle, 5=long press detected):
00032cc8  // - > 2000ms (0x7d0): State 5, long press
00032cc8  // - > 1000ms (0x3e8) and not state 3: State 3, medium press
00032cc8  // Calls button_event_handler(button_id, state) on transitions.
00032cc8  // Implements debouncing and multi-level press detection.
00032cc8  // Called every 50ms from app_timer_handler.
00032cc8  38b5       push    {r3, r4, r5, lr}
00032cca  fbf79ffb   bl      #0x2e40c

00032cd2  0be0       b       #0x32cec

00032cd8  42f82310   str     r1, [r2, r3, lsl #2]
00032cdc  52f82310   ldr     r1, [r2, r3, lsl #2]
00032ce0  c9b2       uxtb    r1, r1

00032ce4  fff71afc   bl      #0x3251c

00032d58    int32_t gpio_button_interrupt_handler(int32_t arg1)

00032d58  // GPIO button interrupt handler - processes hardware button state
00032d58  // changes
00032d58  // arg1: GPIO pin number
00032d58  // Identifies which button based on pin: data_20005d72 or
00032d58  // data_20005d74
00032d58  // Button mapping: button 0, 1, or 2
00032d58  // Reads current pin state from P0.IN, stores in data_200034d4 array
00032d58  // Timestamp handling:
00032d58  // - If state == 2: Uses get_timestamp_ptr()
00032d58  // - Otherwise: Uses get_ptr_200044e0()
00032d58  // - On press (pin low): Stores start timestamp at data_20005d54
00032d58  // - On release (pin high): Calculates duration at data_20005d60
00032d58  // Duration classification:
00032d58  // - 25-1000ms: state 2 (short press)
00032d58  // - 1000-2000ms: state 4 (medium press)
00032d58  // - 2000-3500ms: state 6 (long press)
00032d58  // - <25ms: state 7 (debounce/invalid)
00032d58  // Calls button_event_handler(button_id, press_state)

00032e60    void gpiote_button_event_dispatcher(int32_t arg1)

00032e60  // Dispatch button events to application handler. Called from GPIOTE
00032e60  // ISR when buttons (P0.02/23/24) trigger edge detection. Determines
00032e60  // button ID and press type.
00032e60  08b5       push    {r3, lr}

00032e6e  08bd       pop     {r3, pc}

00032e70  fff772ff   bl      #0x32d58

00032f24  // Temperature bars: g_temperature_celsius mapped to 0-5 bars

00032f24  // 0.00-9999.99mi, 10000-99999mi)

00033ad0    void ui_update_task()

00033ad0  // Main UI update task - renders all LCD screens based on
00033ad0  // data_20005d6f state.
00033ad0  // Implements 20+ screen states:
00033ad0  // 6/8: Main data display with battery arc, speed, mode indicators
00033ad0  // 7: Settings menu (4 options based on data_20005e79)
00033ad0  // 9/0xa: Light/Display settings toggles
00033ad0  // 0xb/0xc/0xd: View/Settings/Navi mode screens
00033ad0  // 0xe: Navigation "ARRIVED!" screen
00033ad0  // 0x14: Firmware update progress screen (shows percentage)
00033ad0  // 0x15/0x16: Update success/failed screens
00033ad0  // 0x17/0x18/0x19: Icon displays
00033ad0  // 0x1c: Battery percentage with arc visualization
00033ad0  // Handles screen transitions, timeouts, auto-sleep logic.
00033ad0  // Calls lcd_refresh() after rendering updates.

000343dc    void app_state_machine()

000343dc  // Main application state machine - runs every loop iteration
000343dc  // Manages app state via data_20005d6f (state byte)
000343dc  // States 0-19 (0x00-0x13) handled:
000343dc  // - State 0/init: Calls app_context_init(0x20005178),
000343dc  // init_comparator()
000343dc  //   Sets data_200034ed=2, data_200034e4=0, transitions to state 2
000343dc  // - State 16 (0x10): Special handling - sets data_200034e0=1
000343dc  // - Default: If data_20005e76==0 (UI update flag):
000343dc  //   * Calls app_scheduler_execute() - process scheduled tasks
000343dc  //   * Calls ui_update_task() - update LCD display
000343dc  //   * Clears data_20005e76 flag
000343dc  //   * On timeout: buttons_deinit(), enter_sleep_mode(0)
000343dc  // 
000343dc  // This is the main state dispatcher that coordinates:
000343dc  // - System initialization
000343dc  // - UI updates
000343dc  // - Sleep/power management
000343dc  // - Button handling
000343dc  // - Display refresh
000343dc  // 
000343dc  // Called from main_app() main loop every iteration
000343dc  30b5       push    {r4, r5, lr}
000343de  a1b0       sub     sp, #0x84
000343e0  184b       ldr     r3, [pc, #0x60]
000343e2  1b78       ldrb    r3, [r3]
000343e4  132b       cmp     r3, #0x13
000343e6  00f2e684   bhi     #0x34db6

000343ea  dfe813f0   tbh     [pc, r3, lsl #1]

00034e44    int32_t lcd_spi_init()

00034e44  // Initialize SPI interface for LCD display
00034e44  // Configures P0.8 as output with pullup (mode 0x203)
00034e44  // SPI config: MISO=-1(disabled), MOSI=8, SCK=6, frequency=0x02000000
00034e44  // (125kHz)
00034e44  // Calls spi_init() with config at 0x200034f4
00034e44  // On success: initializes data at 0x20007ee4 (4x uint16 values to
00034e44  // 0x9c4,0,0,0)
00034e44  // Sends 2-byte init command from 0x47408 via spi_transfer()
00034e44  // On failure: calls reset_entry_point() (system reset)
00034e44  // Critical for LCD communication setup

00034ea8    uint16_t set_backlight_pwm(uint8_t brightness_percent)

00034ea8  // Set LCD backlight brightness via PWM duty cycle.
00034ea8  // Clamps input to 100% max. Formula: (100 - brightness) * 5 +
00034ea8  // additional scaling.
00034ea8  // Lower PWM value = brighter (inverted logic). Stores result in
00034ea8  // data_200034f2.
00034ea8  // From SDK components/drivers_nrf/pwm or app-specific PWM control.
00034ea8  6428       cmp     r0, #0x64
00034eaa  00d9       bls     #0x34eae

00034eac  6420       movs    r0, #0x64

00034ef4    int32_t lcd_send_command(char arg1)

00034ef4  // Send command byte to LCD controller via TWI
00034ef4  // Clears P0.14 (0x4000) - sets D/C line low for command mode
00034ef4  // Calls display_twi_tx_byte(arg1) to send command byte
00034ef4  // Includes small delay loop (countdown from 1) for timing
00034ef4  // Returns result of TWI transmission
00034ef4  08b5       push    {r3, lr}
00034ef6  4ff0a043   mov     r3, #0x50000000
00034efa  4ff48042   mov     r2, #0x4000
00034efe  c3f80c25   str     r2, [r3, #0x50c]
00034f02  faf7f9f8   bl      #0x2f0f8
00034f06  204b       ldr     r3, [pc, #0x80]
00034f08  1a68       ldr     r2, [r3]
00034f0a  0123       movs    r3, #1
00034f0c  1f49       ldr     r1, [pc, #0x7c]

00034f90    int32_t lcd_set_cursor_position(int32_t arg1, char arg2)

00034f90  // Set LCD cursor position for subsequent writes.
00034f90  // Sends 3 commands: column MSB (0x10 + upper nibble), column LSB
00034f90  // (lower nibble),
00034f90  // and page address (arg2 & 0xf - 0x50).
00034f90  // Standard LCD controller cursor positioning sequence.
00034f90  38b5       push    {r3, r4, r5, lr}
00034f92  0546       mov     r5, r0
00034f94  0c46       mov     r4, r1
00034f96  c0f30210   ubfx    r0, r0, #4, #3
00034f9a  1030       adds    r0, #0x10
00034f9c  fff7aaff   bl      #0x34ef4
00034fa0  05f00f00   and     r0, r5, #0xf
00034fa4  fff7a6ff   bl      #0x34ef4
00034fa8  04f00f00   and     r0, r4, #0xf
00034fac  5038       subs    r0, #0x50
00034fae  c0b2       uxtb    r0, r0
00034fb0  fff7a0ff   bl      #0x34ef4
00034fb4  38bd       pop     {r3, r4, r5, pc}

00034fb8    void lcd_clear()

00034fb8  // Clear LCD framebuffer in RAM
00034fb8  // Framebuffer at 0x200076e4 (2048 bytes)
00034fb8  // Loops through 16 rows (0-15), 128 columns (0-127)
00034fb8  // Sets all bytes to 0 (blank screen)
00034fb8  // Does NOT update physical display - call lcd_refresh() after
00034fb8  0020       movs    r0, #0
00034fba  0ae0       b       #0x34fd2

00034fbc  074a       ldr     r2, [pc, #0x1c]
00034fbe  02eb0312   add     r2, r2, r3, lsl #4
00034fc2  0021       movs    r1, #0
00034fc4  1154       strb    r1, [r2, r0]
00034fc6  0133       adds    r3, #1
00034fc8  9bb2       uxth    r3, r3

00034fca  7f2b       cmp     r3, #0x7f
00034fcc  f6d9       bls     #0x34fbc

00034fd0  c0b2       uxtb    r0, r0

00034fd2  0f28       cmp     r0, #0xf
00034fd4  01d8       bhi     #0x34fda

00034fd6  0023       movs    r3, #0
00034fd8  f7e7       b       #0x34fca

00034fda  7047       bx      lr

00034fe0    int32_t lcd_shutdown_sequence()

00034fe0  // entering sleep mode to save power.
00034fe0  08b5       push    {r3, lr}

00035008    uint32_t lcd_set_contrast(uint8_t contrast)

00035008  // Set LCD display contrast level
00035008  // arg1(contrast): Contrast value 0-63 (0x00-0x3f)
00035008  // Sends command 0x81 (Set Contrast) followed by contrast value
00035008  // Uses standard LCD controller command protocol
00035008  // Returns contrast value if valid, unchanged if >63
00035008  3f28       cmp     r0, #0x3f
0003500a  00d9       bls     #0x3500e

0003500c  7047       bx      lr

00035020    int32_t lcd_set_orientation()

00035020  // Set LCD display orientation based on data_20005d70.
00035020  // Mode 1: 0xa0 + 0xc0 (normal orientation)
00035020  // Other: 0xa1 + 0xc8 (180 rotated)
00035020  // Controls segment remap and COM output scan direction.
00035020  08b5       push    {r3, lr}
00035022  fdf70df9   bl      #0x32240
00035026  0378       ldrb    r3, [r0]
00035028  012b       cmp     r3, #1
0003502a  06d0       beq     #0x3503a

0003502c  a120       movs    r0, #0xa1
0003502e  fff761ff   bl      #0x34ef4
00035032  c820       movs    r0, #0xc8
00035034  fff75eff   bl      #0x34ef4

00035038  08bd       pop     {r3, pc}

00035048    uint32_t lcd_refresh()

00035048  // Refresh LCD display from framebuffer
00035048  // Framebuffer at 0x200076e4 (128x64 pixels = 16x128 bytes)
00035048  // Rotates framebuffer 90 degrees for display orientation
00035048  // Loops through 16 rows (0-15), 128 columns (0-127)
00035048  // Reads bits from framebuffer, packs into bytes for TWI transmission
00035048  // Calls lcd_set_cursor_position(0,0) then display_twi_tx_buffer()
00035048  // Critical function for updating physical display from memory
00035048  70b5       push    {r4, r5, r6, lr}
0003504a  adf5016d   sub     sp, sp, #0x810
0003504e  4ff40162   mov     r2, #0x810
00035052  0021       movs    r1, #0
00035054  6846       mov     r0, sp
00035056  eef769f9   bl      #0x2332c

0003505e  7446       mov     r4, lr

00035068  11d8       bhi     #0x3508e

00035070  1b48       ldr     r0, [pc, #0x6c]
00035072  00eb0111   add     r1, r0, r1, lsl #4
00035076  8a5c       ldrb    r2, [r1, r2]
00035078  a5eb0c01   sub     r1, r5, r12
0003507c  0a41       asrs    r2, r1
0003507e  12f0010f   tst     r2, #1
00035082  eed0       beq     #0x35062

00035084  0122       movs    r2, #1
00035086  9a40       lsls    r2, r3
00035088  3243       orrs    r2, r6
0003508a  d6b2       uxtb    r6, r2
0003508c  e9e7       b       #0x35062

0003508e  0df80460   strb    r6, [sp, r4]
00035092  0134       adds    r4, #1
00035094  a4b2       uxth    r4, r4
00035096  0135       adds    r5, #1
00035098  edb2       uxtb    r5, r5

0003509e  0ad1       bne     #0x350b6

00035a58    void lcd_draw_text(uint16_t x, uint16_t y, uint8_t color, char* text, uint8_t font_id)

00035a58  // Draw text string on LCD framebuffer
00035a58  // arg1(x): X position, 0x80 = auto-center
00035a58  // arg2(y): Y position in pixels
00035a58  // arg3(color): Font type/table selector:
00035a58  //   0=2byte (small), 1=4byte (medium), 2=6byte_symbols, 3=8byte_large
00035a58  // (numbers)
00035a58  //   5=3byte_large, 6=6byte_numeric, 7=6byte_numeric_mirrored,
00035a58  // 8=3byte_medium, 9=overlay_4byte
00035a58  // arg4(text): Null-terminated text string pointer
00035a58  // arg5(font_id): Vertical centering height (0x80 - centered)
00035a58  // Calculates text width from font tables, centers horizontally if
00035a58  // x=0x80
00035a58  // Clears background area if font_id specified
00035a58  // Calls font-specific draw functions (lcd_draw_font_*) for each
00035a58  // character
00035a58  // Adds 2-6 pixel spacing between characters based on font type
00035a58  2de9f047   push    {r4, r5, r6, r7, r8, r9, r10, lr}

00036708    uint32_t ext_flash_write_data(char* arg1, int32_t arg2, uint32_t arg3)

00036708  // Write data to external SPI flash via TWI interface.
00036708  // Sends write command sequence:
00036708  // - CS low, command 0x12 (or 0x02 based on data_20008313)

00036908    int32_t ext_flash_chip_erase()

00036908  // Erase entire external SPI flash chip
00036908  // SDK: Application-specific (external flash driver)
00036908  // 
00036908  // Performs bulk erase of external SPI flash memory chip.
00036908  // 
00036908  // External flash chip:
00036908  // - Type: IS25LP/GD25 series SPI NOR flash (likely IS25LP064 or
00036908  // similar)
00036908  // - Capacity: Typically 8MB (64Mbit) based on firmware update sizes
00036908  // - Interface: SPI (MOSI, MISO, SCK, CS pins)
00036908  // - Erase granularity: 4KB subsectors, 64KB sectors, or full chip
00036908  // 
00036908  // Chip erase command sequence:
00036908  // 1. Send WREN (0x06): Write Enable command
00036908  // 2. Wait for WEL bit in status register
00036908  // 3. Send CE (0xC7 or 0x60): Chip Erase command
00036908  // 4. Poll status register until WIP (Write In Progress) bit clears
00036908  // 5. Erase time: Typically 20-50 seconds for full 8MB chip
00036908  // 
00036908  // Status register polling:
00036908  // - RDSR (0x05): Read Status Register
00036908  // - WIP bit (0x01): Write/erase in progress
00036908  // - WEL bit (0x02): Write enable latch
00036908  // 
00036908  // Use cases:
00036908  // - Factory reset: Erase all STM firmware images
00036908  // - Firmware update preparation: Clear flash before writing new image
00036908  // - Storage cleanup: Remove all diagnostic logs
00036908  // - Development: Clear flash for testing
00036908  // 
00036908  // IMPORTANT: Blocks for 20-50 seconds!
00036908  // - Must feed watchdog during erase
00036908  // - Consider using sector erase for partial cleanup
00036908  // 
00036908  // Called from: Factory reset handler, firmware update initialization
00036908  // 
00036908  // Returns: Status code (0 on success)
00036908  10b5       push    {r4, lr}
0003690a  0024       movs    r4, #0

0003690c  fff782ff   bl      #0x36814
00036910  28b9       cbnz    r0, #0x3691e

00036912  631c       adds    r3, r4, #1
00036914  dbb2       uxtb    r3, r3
00036916  052c       cmp     r4, #5
00036918  0ed0       beq     #0x36938

0003691a  1c46       mov     r4, r3
0003691c  f6e7       b       #0x3690c

0003691e  f8f73dfc   bl      #0x2f19c
00036922  6020       movs    r0, #0x60
00036924  fff7ebfe   bl      #0x366fe
00036928  f8f73efc   bl      #0x2f1a8
0003692c  f9f7a2fa   bl      #0x2fe74
00036930  0248       ldr     r0, [pc, #8]
00036932  fff77dff   bl      #0x36830
00036936  00e0       b       #0x3693a

00036938  0120       movs    r0, #1

0003693a  10bd       pop     {r4, pc}

0003693c  int32_t data_3693c = 0x493e0

00036d68    int32_t ext_flash_get_sector_address(int32_t* arg1, int32_t arg2)

00036d68  // Calculate start address of flash sector from sector number.
00036d68  // Flash has 3 regions with different sector sizes
00036d68  // (data_20008318/1e/22).
00036d68  // Region 1: sectors 0 to data_2000831c-1
00036d68  // Region 2: sectors data_2000831c to data_2000831c+data_20008320-1
00036d68  // Region 3: remaining sectors
00036d68  // Returns address via arg1 pointer. Returns 0 on success, 1/2 on
00036d68  // error.

00037228    int32_t ext_flash_erase_all_sectors()

00037228  // Erase all sectors in external flash
00037228  // SDK: Application-specific (external flash driver)
00037228  // 
00037228  // Erases all sectors in external SPI flash memory.
00037228  // Alternative to ext_flash_chip_erase() with sector-by-sector
00037228  // control.
00037228  // 
00037228  // Sector structure:
00037228  // - Sector 0-127: 64KB sectors (typical for 8MB chip)
00037228  // - Total: 128 sectors  64KB = 8MB
00037228  // - Each sector: 0x10000 bytes (65536 bytes)
00037228  // 
00037228  // Erase process:
00037228  // 1. Iterate through all sector indices (0 to max_sector)
00037228  // 2. For each sector:
00037228  //    - Call ext_flash_erase_sector_at_index(i)
00037228  //    - Send SE (0xD8): Sector Erase command with address
00037228  //    - Wait for WIP bit to clear (~200-500ms per sector)
00037228  // 3. Feed watchdog periodically to prevent reset
00037228  // 
00037228  // Advantages over chip erase:
00037228  // - Finer control: Can stop early if needed
00037228  // - Progress tracking: Know which sector being erased
00037228  // - Watchdog friendly: Can feed WDT between sectors
00037228  // - Interruptible: Can abort if necessary
00037228  // 
00037228  // Erase time calculation:
00037228  // - Per sector: ~200-500ms
00037228  // - Total time: 128 sectors  500ms = 64 seconds maximum
00037228  // 
00037228  // Use cases:
00037228  // - Factory reset with progress indication
00037228  // - Firmware update preparation
00037228  // - Diagnostic log cleanup
00037228  // - Development testing
00037228  // 
00037228  // Called from: Factory reset state machine, firmware update
00037228  // initialization
00037228  // 
00037228  // Returns: Status code (0 on success)
00037228  10b5       push    {r4, lr}
0003722a  82b0       sub     sp, #8
0003722c  0024       movs    r4, #0

0003722e  fff7f1fa   bl      #0x36814
00037232  28b9       cbnz    r0, #0x37240

00037234  631c       adds    r3, r4, #1
00037236  dbb2       uxtb    r3, r3
00037238  052c       cmp     r4, #5
0003723a  17d0       beq     #0x3726c

0003723c  1c46       mov     r4, r3
0003723e  f6e7       b       #0x3722e

00037240  0023       movs    r3, #0
00037242  adf80630   strh    r3, [sp, #6]
00037246  0121       movs    r1, #1

00037248  bdf80620   ldrh    r2, [sp, #6]
0003724c  094b       ldr     r3, [pc, #0x24]
0003724e  1b88       ldrh    r3, [r3]
00037250  9bb2       uxth    r3, r3
00037252  9a42       cmp     r2, r3
00037254  0bd8       bhi     #0x3726e

00037256  0df10600   add     r0, sp, #6
0003725a  fff7b5ff   bl      #0x371c8
0003725e  0146       mov     r1, r0
00037260  28b9       cbnz    r0, #0x3726e

00037262  bdf80630   ldrh    r3, [sp, #6]
00037266  002b       cmp     r3, #0
00037268  eed1       bne     #0x37248

0003726a  00e0       b       #0x3726e

0003726c  0121       movs    r1, #1

0003726e  0846       mov     r0, r1
00037270  02b0       add     sp, #8
00037272  10bd       pop     {r4, pc}

00037278    int32_t ext_flash_write_frame(char* arg1, int32_t* arg2, int32_t arg3, int32_t arg4)

00037278  // needed.

0003746c    uint32_t ext_flash_read_next_frame(void* arg1)

0003746c  // Read next framed message from external flash.
0003746c  // Searches for "ml###" frame header starting at data_20008340.
0003746c  // Validates:
0003746c  // - Magic bytes 0x6d, 0x6c ("ml")
0003746c  // - 3 ASCII decimal digits for length (max 250)
0003746c  // - All payload bytes pass is_valid_display_char check
0003746c  // Handles sector boundaries, wraps to 0 if exceeds data_2000832c.
0003746c  // Updates data_20008340 read position, data_2000834c sector.
0003746c  // Copies payload to arg1, returns status code.
0003746c  // Returns: 0=EOF/empty, 1=no valid frame, 2=success, 0x10+=success
0003746c  // with sector.

00037a50    uint32_t ext_flash_find_last_write_position(int32_t* arg1, int32_t arg2, int32_t arg3)

00037a50  // Find last written position in external flash
00037a50  // SDK: Application-specific (external flash driver)
00037a50  // 
00037a50  // Searches flash to find end of written data (STM firmware image).
00037a50  // 
00037a50  // Search algorithm:
00037a50  // 1. Read first bytes of each sector to check for data
00037a50  // 2. Binary search within sectors to find exact write position
00037a50  // 3. Look for 0xff bytes (erased state) to identify boundary
00037a50  // 4. Return address of last written byte
00037a50  // 
00037a50  // Data structure detection:
00037a50  // - "ml###" frame markers at boundaries
00037a50  // - Firmware header at start (magic, size, version)
00037a50  // - Padding bytes (0xff) after valid data
00037a50  // 
00037a50  // Use cases:
00037a50  // - Resume interrupted firmware write
00037a50  // - Determine if firmware complete
00037a50  // - Calculate firmware size for verification
00037a50  // - Prepare for next write operation
00037a50  // 
00037a50  // Firmware write flow:
00037a50  // 1. Erase flash sectors
00037a50  // 2. Write firmware data in chunks
00037a50  // 3. On interruption: ext_flash_find_last_write_position()
00037a50  // 4. Resume write from found position
00037a50  // 
00037a50  // Write position states:
00037a50  // - 0x000000: Flash empty, no firmware written
00037a50  // - 0x000000-0x7fffff: Partial write, can resume
00037a50  // - End of valid data: Complete firmware, ready for DFU
00037a50  // 
00037a50  // Parameters:
00037a50  // - arg1: uint32_t* output pointer for last write address
00037a50  // 
00037a50  // Returns: Status code, updates output with address
00037a50  // Related: ext_flash_find_read_position() for STM DFU reading
00037a50  2de9f043   push    {r4, r5, r6, r7, r8, r9, lr}
00037a54  c5b0       sub     sp, #0x114
00037a56  0646       mov     r6, r0

00037a5a  1446       mov     r4, r2
00037a5c  0df10e00   add     r0, sp, #0xe

00037de0    int32_t ext_flash_detect_chip(char* arg1)

00037de0  // Detect and identify external SPI flash chip
00037de0  // SDK: Application-specific (external flash driver)
00037de0  // 
00037de0  // Reads flash chip identification and initializes chip-specific
00037de0  // parameters.
00037de0  // 
00037de0  // Detection sequence:
00037de0  // 1. Send RDID (0x9F): Read Identification command
00037de0  // 2. Read 3 bytes: [Manufacturer ID, Memory Type, Capacity]
00037de0  // 3. Parse identification bytes
00037de0  // 4. Configure chip parameters based on detected chip
00037de0  // 
00037de0  // Common flash chips:
00037de0  // - IS25LP064/128: ISSI (0x9D, 0x60, 0x17/0x18)
00037de0  // - GD25Q64/128: GigaDevice (0xC8, 0x40, 0x17/0x18)
00037de0  // - W25Q64/128: Winbond (0xEF, 0x40, 0x17/0x18)
00037de0  // 
00037de0  // Capacity byte encoding (byte 3):
00037de0  // - 0x17: 64Mbit (8MB)
00037de0  // - 0x18: 128Mbit (16MB)
00037de0  // - 0x19: 256Mbit (32MB)
00037de0  // 
00037de0  // Parameters configured:
00037de0  // - Total sectors: capacity / 64KB
00037de0  // - Sector size: 64KB (0x10000)
00037de0  // - Subsector size: 4KB (0x1000)
00037de0  // - Page size: 256 bytes (for programming)
00037de0  // - Status register layout
00037de0  // - Command set (standard JEDEC mostly)
00037de0  // 
00037de0  // Stored at: data_20008400 (flash chip info structure)
00037de0  // 
00037de0  // Error handling:
00037de0  // - If RDID fails or returns 0x00/0xff: Flash not detected
00037de0  // - If unknown manufacturer: Use default parameters
00037de0  // - If chip unsupported: Return error code
00037de0  // 
00037de0  // Returns: 0 on success, error code if detection failed
00037de0  // Called from: ext_flash_init() during initialization
00037de0  f0b5       push    {r4, r5, r6, r7, lr}

00038128    uint32_t enter_sleep_mode(int32_t arg1)

00038128  // Enter deep sleep mode with external flash cleanup
00038128  // arg1: Mode selector (0 or non-zero affects behavior)
00038128  // Early exit if arg1!=0 OR data_200082f4 bit 2 set
00038128  // 
00038128  // Sleep preparation sequence:
00038128  // 1. Clears state flags: data_200082f5=0, data_2000857d=0,
00038128  // data_20008564=0
00038128  // 2. Sets data_20003500=3 (sleep mode state)
00038128  // 3. Clears bit 2 of data_200082f4
00038128  // 
00038128  // If data_200082f5==5 (special state):
00038128  // - Writes pending external flash data if data_20008580 set
00038128  // - Erases subsectors at data_20008570, writes header
00038128  // - Writes pending data if data_2000857e set
00038128  // - Erases subsectors at data_200082fc, writes header
00038128  // - Handles data_2000857f flag with erase/write
00038128  // 
00038128  // If data_200082f5 > 10:
00038128  // - Sets data_200082f5=6 (fallback state)
00038128  // 
00038128  // Cleanup phase:
00038128  // - Clears 22 bytes at 0x20008310
00038128  // - Clears 16 bytes at 0x200082f8 and 0x2000856c
00038128  // - Zeros 12+ state variables (timestamps, buffers, flags)
00038128  // - Turns off display backlight via display_backlight_off()
00038128  // - Delays 10ms via delay_ms(0xa)
00038128  // - Sets data_200082f5=1 (sleep state)
00038128  // 
00038128  // Returns current sleep state
00038128  // Critical for low power operation and external flash persistence
00038128  40bb       cbnz    r0, #0x3817c

000388e0    int32_t check_nrf52832_chip_variant()

000388e0  // Verify nRF52832 chip variant from FICR registers.
000388e0  // Reads 0xf0000fe0 (expecting 6), 0xf0000fe4 (expecting 0xN0),
000388e0  // 0xf0000fe8.
000388e0  // Accepts variants with bits [7:4] = 0x3, 0x4, or 0x5 (QFAA
000388e0  // E0/G0/variants).
000388e0  // Returns 1 if valid QFAA variant, 0 otherwise.
000388e0  // Used during initialization to verify compatible hardware.
000388e0  4ff07043   mov     r3, #0xf0000000
000388e4  93f8e03f   ldrb    r3, [r3, #0xfe0]
000388e8  062b       cmp     r3, #6
000388ea  01d0       beq     #0x388f0

000388ec  0020       movs    r0, #0
000388ee  7047       bx      lr

000388f0  4ff07043   mov     r3, #0xf0000000

00038b74    int32_t check_ficr_nfc_pins()

00038b74  // Check if NFC pins are available from FICR configuration.
00038b74  // Reads FICR registers at offset 0x130 and 0x134.
00038b74  // Returns 1 if both registers == 6 (NFC pins available as GPIO).
00038b74  // Returns 0 otherwise (NFC functionality disabled).
00038b74  // Used to determine if P0.09/P0.10 available for GPIO.
00038b74  4ff08053   mov     r3, #0x10000000
00038b78  d3f83031   ldr     r3, [r3, #0x130]
00038b7c  062b       cmp     r3, #6
00038b7e  01d0       beq     #0x38b84

00038b80  0020       movs    r0, #0
00038b82  7047       bx      lr

00038b84  4ff08053   mov     r3, #0x10000000
00038b88  d3f83431   ldr     r3, [r3, #0x134]
00038b8c  062b       cmp     r3, #6
00038b8e  01d0       beq     #0x38b94

00038ba8    int32_t SystemInit()

00038ba8  // ARM CMSIS: System initialization (clock, FPU, etc.) before main()
00038ba8  08b5       push    {r3, lr}
00038baa  fff799fe   bl      #0x388e0
00038bae  40b1       cbz     r0, #0x38bc2

00038bb0  4ff08053   mov     r3, #0x10000000
00038bb4  d3f82433   ldr     r3, [r3, #0x324]
00038bb8  c3f30423   ubfx    r3, r3, #8, #5
00038bbc  8f4a       ldr     r2, [pc, #0x23c]
00038bbe  c2f84035   str     r3, [r2, #0x540]

00038bc2  fff7b2fe   bl      #0x3892a
00038bc6  10b1       cbz     r0, #0x38bce

00039730    void* vfprintf(int32_t* arg1, int32_t** arg2, char* arg3, int32_t* arg4, int32_t* arg5 @ r6)

00039730  // vfprintf implementation - parses printf format strings and handles
00039730  // format specifiers (%d, %s, %c, %x, etc.), flags (#-0+ ), field
00039730  // width, precision, length modifiers (hlL). ARM compiler C library
00039730  // function.
00039730  2de9f04f   push    {r4, r5, r6, r7, r8, r9, r10, r11, lr}

00039736  8b89       ldrh    r3, [r1, #0xc]
00039738  1b06       lsls    r3, r3, #0x18
0003973a  9db0       sub     sp, #0x74
0003973c  0746       mov     r7, r0
0003973e  0d46       mov     r5, r1
00039740  1446       mov     r4, r2
00039742  0ed5       bpl     #0x39762
